Do what I did.... contact some of the local horse groups and
offer to help desensitize their animals. I even boarded two llamas
at one stable that had rentals. The llamas were in a small pen
near the horses feeding area (but always separate from the
horses). If the horses wanted to eat they had to go near the
llamas. After a few days all were buddies.

Ask about the local &quot;trail trials&quot; group. In several events a
llama and I were an obstacle in their course. I was invited to
the state finals where they gave me a deluxe campsite and fed me,
and the llama, too well. The llama was quite a hit and I think I
convinced a few tough horsemen that these animals are not trail
poodles.
--
Dave

