I've owned horses for 25 years and am a member of a local horseman's
club. I've already discussed with the club president an &quot;intro to
camelids&quot; presentation at our September meeting. I wrote and submitted
an article to the Horseman's Corral, a statewide equestrian newspaper
published by the Ohio Horseman's Council (OHC). (No guarantees of
publication, though.) I contacted the president of the OHC with a
notice, too. However, he hasn't responded.

The idea of putting out a couple llamas in a pipe corral near horses
at stables is intriguing. I'll have to think about that one before
approaching the stable owners. There are no livery stables in my area;
all are private breeding, training, and/or boarding stables.

