I just sent an invitation this morning to the leader of the local 4-H
camelid club. I think she'll take me up on it. I also offered to visit
the local camelid club (4-H or otherwise) to give an &quot;intro to horses&quot;
presentation. One of the things the camelid people could do to
facilitate acceptance (instead of resentment) is to pitch in and help
with trail/campground building and maintenance. Equestrian trails in
Ohio state parks, for the most part, are built and maintained by
equestrian *volunteers*. Extra hands to help in that work will be
really appreciated. Basically, if camelid owners are going to use the
bridle trails, then they can help maintain them. That will build a
solid, working partnership.

I want to make the trail sharing as cooperative and collaborative as
possible.

--Karen Smith
